The Story of
/$
$
Froggy's Saloon
/$
$
Froggy's Saloon in Daytona Beach has a rich history as a beloved destination for motorcycle enthusiasts.  Opened in the 1990s, it quickly became a popular spot for both locals and visitors, known for its laid-back atmosphere, beautiful women, and cold drinks. Located just a short distance from the iconic Daytona Beach, Froggy's earned a reputation for being a biker-friendly bar that welcome riders from all over the world, especially during major events like Bike Week and Biketoberfest. The saloon’s unique charm comes from its blend of traditional local bar vibes with a focus on motorcycle culture, offering a place to relax, enjoy a drink, and connect with fellow bikers. Over time, Froggy's has become an iconic watering hole in Daytona Beach, representing the city's vibrant atmosphere, especially for those who visit for its famous motorsport events .
/$

History of Bike Week
/$
$
Daytona Bike Week, established in 1937, is one of the largest and most iconic motorcycle events in the United States. It was originally a gathering of motorcycle enthusiasts who participated in racing events at Daytona Beach. The event's roots trace back to the formation of the Daytona 200, a prestigious motorcycle race, which quickly became a staple of the week’s festivities. Over the decades, Daytona Bike Week grew exponentially, attracting riders from all over the world for a mix of racing, bike shows, concerts, and scenic rides along the coast. The event became a cultural landmark, symbolizing the freedom and camaraderie of motorcycling, while also expanding to include vendors, custom bike builders, and a range of entertainment. Today, Daytona Bike Week spans over 10 days and draws hundreds of thousands of visitors annually, making it a must-attend celebration for motorcyclists of all kinds.

800 Main Street
/$
$
800 Main Street in Daytona Beach, Florida, is home to a historic building that has played a significant role in the city's rich cultural and social landscape.  Originally built in the early 20th century, the building was home to the East Coast Bank and trust co. and then later used by the US treasury.  Since then the building has seen various iterations and functions over the years.  One of the most notable chapters in its history was when it became the home of the popular Froggy's Saloon, a favorite spot for both locals and out-of-town visitors.   The building's long history reflects Daytona's transformation into a major cultural and tourist destination while maintaining a strong connection to its roots in motorsport and beach culture.
​

Upcoming Events
/$
$
/$
$
$
$
Race Week 2025
Feb 12 - 16
/$
$
Experience the thrill of the Daytona 500, one of the most spectacular events in motorsports. Feel the adrenaline the cars race around the track, showcasing incredible speed and skill. After the race, unwind at Froggy's Saloon, where you can enjoy a refreshing drink and soak in the lively atmosphere. It's the perfect way to celebrate an exhilarating day at the races!
/$
$
/$
/$
$
$
Turkey Rod Run '25
March 21 - 23
/$
$
Turkey Rod Run is an annual celebration for classic car enthusiasts, with its impressive display of vintage cars, hot rods, and muscle machines.  After a day of exploring the stunning cars, head to Froggy's Saloon for a well-deserved drink. The laid-back vibe, great drinks, makes Froggy's an ideal spot to unwind and reflect on the day’s festivities.
/$
$
/$
/$
$
$
Rockville 2025
May 15 - 18
​
/$
$
Rockville Daytona Beach is a high-energy, rock music festival that draws fans from all over, offering an unforgettable experience with live performances from iconic bands and up-and-coming artists. After rocking out to your favorite tunes, swing by Froggy's Saloon for a cold drink and a chance to unwind. With its relaxed vibe and friendly crowd, Froggy's is the perfect spot to keep the good times rolling and chat about the day’s musical highlights.
/$
$
/$
/$
$
$
Biketoberfest 2025
Oct 16 - 19
/$
$
Biketoberfest in Daytona Beach is an epic weekend filled with motorcycle rallies, thrilling rides, and a  vibrant atmosphere on Main Street that brings bikers together from all over.  With its great drink selection, live dancers,  beautiful bartenders and fun crowd, Froggy's is the perfect place to keep the energy high and soak in the Biketoberfest vibe. It’s the ultimate spot to unwind and enjoy the weekend with fellow riders.
/$
$
/$
/$
$
$
Bike Week 2025
Feb 28 - Mar 6
/$
$
Daytona Bike Week, where motorcycle enthusiasts gather to celebrate the open road. After a day filled with excitement, make your way to Froggy's Saloon, a vibrant spot known for its lively atmosphere refreshing drinks, and beautiful bartenders. Froggy's the perfect place to unwind and connect with fellow bikers. Embrace the spirit of the event and create unforgettable memories at this iconic venue!
/$
$
/$
/$
$
$
Jeep Week
April 18 - 27
/$
$
Daytona Beach Jeep Week is the ultimate event for Jeep lovers, with thrilling scenic drives and a vibrant community of Jeep enthusiasts. As you explore the rugged vehicles and enjoy the exciting festivities, make sure to stop by Froggy's Saloon afterward for a cold beverage. Froggy's offers a relaxed atmosphere, perfect for unwinding after a day of Jeep-filled fun, with refreshing drinks and great company to top off your day.
/$

/$
$
$
Coke Zero 400
Aug 23
/$
$
Attending a NASCAR race in Daytona is an adrenaline-packed experience with the roar of engines with high-speed action, and thrilling competition makes every lap exciting. After the race, head to Froggy's Saloon to cool down and celebrate the day. Our welcoming atmosphere and drink selection make Froggy's  the perfect spot to relax, unwind, and chat about the race. An ideal way to cap off an unforgettable Daytona experience.
